data.title: Minneapolis StarTribune
data.meta_description: Minneapolis StarTribune - a place for remembering loved ones; a space for sharing memories, life stories, milestones, to express condolences, and celebrate life of your loved ones
data.text:
Dean Custer

Custer, Dean R. age 91, of Annandale, formerly of Fridley, died Sun., Aug. 11, 2024. Memorial Service 11:00 a.m. Mon, Aug. 19, at Dingmann Funeral Care Chapel, Annandale. Visitation one hour prior to the service. Burial at St. Mary's Cemetery, Waverly. www.dingmannfuneral.com

Gary Eisenschenk

Eisenschenk, Gary John age 59, passed away unexpectedly on August 11, 2024, in Clayton, WI. Services will be held on Friday, August 16, 2024 at Church of the Assumption in Saint Paul, MN. Visitation will begin at 9 am with mass to follow at 10 am. There will be a Celebration of Life on Sunday, August 18 at the...

Paul Erickson

Erickson, Paul R. 67, of Prior Lake, passed Aug 10, 2024. Time of Gathering 5 - 7 PM Thurs, Aug 15, 2024 at Ballard- Sunder Funeral Home Prior Lake (4565 Pleasant St). Funeral Service 11:00 AM with visitation prior 10:00 - 11:00 AM Fri, Aug 16, 2024 Hometown Church in Lakeville (16165 Kenwood Trail)....

Lillian Gould

Gould, Lillian E. Age 104 of Inver Grove Heights, formerly of South St. Paul. Passed away peacefully on August 12, 2024. Preceded in death by husband, Jay; 4 brothers and 4 sisters. Survived by son, Jeff (Wendy); daughter, Debbie; grandson, James (Laura); also other relatives and friends. Lillian lived a...

Carol Hayden

Hayden, Carol Schwarting Carol passed away surrounded by her loving family on July 27, following a stroke. She lived a remarkable 90 years and leaves behind a vast network of friends and family who already miss her kind presence, sparkling eyes, and thought-provoking questions. Carol was raised in Hecla, SD,...

Jane Holbrook

Jane Stoddard Brown Holbrook, 94, died March 21, 2024, Charlottesville, Virginia. She was born to Roger and Helen Brown August 18,1929, in East Haven, Connecticut. She attended University of Connecticut and received a teacher certificate. She married William I. Holbrook on August 14, 1954, and they raised their...

Kathryn Holmes

Holmes, Kathryn M. Surrounded by her children, Kathryn ("Kathi") Mayleen Lundstrom Holmes, age 78, passed away in the early morning hours of August 9, 2024. Kathi was born in Brooklyn, New York and grew up in Richfield, Minnesota. She graduated from West High School in Minneapolis and earned her B.A....

Rosemary Jackson

Jackson, Rosemary J. (Forsberg) 86, Scottsdale, AZ, also of Robbinsdale and Laporte, MN. Passed away on October 27, 2023. Beloved wife, mother, grandmother, and great-grandmother. Preceded in death by her parents, Russell and Kathryn Forsberg; her husband, John Jackson; and sister Patricia. Survived by her...

Ingrid Erica White

Ingrid Erica White June 17, 1977 to August 12, 2014 Though you are no longer with us, you will never be forgotten.

Jan Boylan

Four years and still deeply missed "so much bad." Until we meet again mama, may you sing with the angels and continue to feel our love

Jill & Kelly

ELEANOR I. WALIOR

ELEANOR I. WALIOR Dec. 29, 1938 - Aug. 8, 2011 Forever in our hearts; your memories are treasured every day. Your husband, children, grandchildren, family and friends miss you

KEN "KENNY" CZUPTA

KEN "KENNY" CZUPTA Aug. 5, 1968 Aug. 20, 2006 Hi Ken, Tomorrow would be your 56th Birthday, August 5, 1968. You were actually born on a Monday. Wishing you a very Happy Birthday. Love, Love, Love You! Mom, David, Cindy, Family & Friends

Adam Engman-Delforge

Adam Engman-Delforge 8/4/80 - 3/28/03 "If I could turn back time, If I could find a way, If I could reach the stars, I'd give 'em all to you." I remember you every day, but especially on your birthday. Love you forever, Your Mother

Brian Toivonen

Brian Toivonen Happy Birthday! Love Always, Mom XOXO "May you see the reflection of your life's kindness and beauty in all the tears that fall for you." Send a kid skiing - http://Give.RidingOnInsulin.org/brian

Joy Whipps

In Memory of Joy Whipps 10/7/46 - 7/31/04 It's been 20 years since you left us. Time has gone so fast but our love has not. We will always love you. Love, Bob and best friend Patricia.

Raymond B. Anthony

Raymond B. Anthony March 11, 1952 - July 29, 2022 My little brother and best friend. I miss our weekly phone calls when we discussed every topic under the sun. I miss your willingness to always help others and how you always looked out for me. You will always be in our hearts.
